  "text": "Human umbilical vein endothelial cells (HUVECs) were purchased from the American Type Culture Collection (Manassas, VA, USA) and cultured using EGM-2 MV Bullet kits (Lonza, Inc.) containing 1% penicillin/streptomycin and maintained at 37°C in 5% CO 2 . VSMCs were isolated from 3-week-old Sprague-Dawley rats by a tissue explanting method. The thoracic aorta was isolated and surrounding fat and connective tissues were discarded. Vessels were cut longitudinally and the lumen side was scraped with a razor blade to remove the intima. Vessels were fragmented into lengths of 3-5 mm and explanted lumen side down on collagen-coated culture dishes. After 7 days of explanting, tissue fragments were discarded and sprouted VSMCs were collected and used (passage 2-3) for the experiments. A precise description of the method is provided in a previous study [CITATION_1] .",
